## DIY and inertia competitors appear earliest in mid-market

In mid-market accounts, loss narratives often started as "we can build this" or
"current process is good enough" before named vendor competition appeared.

Fact: Early-stage competitive risk frequently manifested as DIY or do-nothing positioning.
Belief: Competitive monitoring should treat inertia as a first-class competitor pattern.
Value: Counter-positioning should focus on time-to-value and operational reliability.
Precedent: Deals reframed around implementation burden were more likely to recover.
